indings with the results of\nrelativistic MHD simulations and observed gravitational waves we conclude that\nprogenitor neutron stars were old, had close masses and highly reduced magnetic\nfields. In addition, they probably had oppositely directed spins due to the\nencounter and gravitational interaction with other stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 May 2019 17:32:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-23"}
