f an oblate system. Their\nvelocity is nearly systemic, and we conclude that these shells are\nphase-wrapped. For the third one (NGCB3934) the shells appear to participate to\nthe rotation, and follow up with higher spatial resolution is required to\nconclude.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 May 2019 17:33:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Aug 2019 16:09:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-02"}
